title: Album Page, "City Gate, Basel", September 27, 1887
medium: Graphite on cream paperboard tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, clockwise from top center: Roof in black white an yellow; (inscribed in circle) 54 / 66; Basel / Sept 27th 1887.
description: Vertical sheet with one sketch of a Romanesque gate.  The masonry gate has a small archway at its base, two stair turrets at either corner with crenellation at their tops, a high peaked roof in the center, and a clock on its façade.

tombstone.epitaph:
Album Page, "City Gate, Basel", September 27, 1887.
September 27, 1887. Graphite on cream paperboard tipped into binding with fabric. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1943-51-134.
